-- Online Holiday Spending More Than $21.95 Billion in 40 Days, Comscore Says
-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 2010-12-12T17:57:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/online-holiday-spending-more-than-21-95-billion-in-40-days-comscore-says.html
U.S. online sales for the first 40
days of the holiday shopping season are about $22 billion, up 12
percent for the same period last year, ComScore Inc. said in a
PR Newswire statement.  Sales gained 11 percent during the past week ended
yesterday to $5.15 billion, the retail tracking company said.
Two of the days during the week topped $900 million each.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Hart at 
